original issue: https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-6525

h3. Issue summary

When performing a search on the customer portal, if any relevant request types are found, they are listed in the results. Underneath these results, the following Dutch sentence is mentioned:
{quote}
Geen van deze oplossing helpen mij
{quote}

It is an incorrect Dutch translation.

h3. Suggested Resolution

An example of correct translation should be:
{quote}
Met geen van deze oplossing(en) ben ik geholpen.
{quote}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6399].
  {panel}

If a Confluence page has file attachments with Japanese file names and you click on them one-by-one, they get downloaded to the local disk and the Japanese file name is preserved (except that spaces " " get replaced by a "+" see CONF-4503). However, if you click on "download all", the file names of the downloaded files are corrupted on the local disk.  Please see screenshots attached. I was able to replicate this problem on Windows using IE browser (worked fine on Mac Safari). I think this could be an issue for many of our Japanese customers.

There are untranslated strings on Project default board for all the projects created from template (screens attached). This issue is global and is present for all the languages.

It seems that the strings are hardcoded in {color:#172b4d} jira-cloud/jira-components/jira-plugins/jira-project-templates-plugin/jira-core-project-templates/src/main/resources/images/svg . {color} 

{color:#172b4d}The strings are missing in Transifex and appear in English despite of the provisioning language is different. In the attachments you can see the English string in the Jira instance provisioned in Japanese for a google account with Russian default settings.{color}
